Ad Text:
I’m working with a growing, community-focused organisation investing heavily in its data capability. This role will play a key part in shaping their Azure data environment and enterprise warehouse.
 
Responsibilities

Design and maintain Azure data pipelines;
Lead data modelling and architecture;
Support enterprise data warehouse development;
Implement data governance across Azure;
Work closely with stakeholders to deliver practical solutions; and
Contribute to CI/CD and DevOps practices.
Key Skills

5+ years’ Azure data engineering experience;
Strong Azure Data Factory & Databricks expertise;
Advanced Python & SQL;
ETL, data modelling and governance experience; and
Experience ingesting data from multiple sources.
How to Apply
 
For more information or a confidential discussion please call Madison Wiles at u&u on 0431 475 714 quoting reference number 44345.
 
At u&u Recruitment Partners, we value diversity, equity and inclusion. We welcome applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds and people with disability.
 
Should you require reasonable adjustments or have a preferred method of communication throughout the recruitment process, we encourage you to make a request via adjustments@uandu.com or phone the above-mentioned u&u consultant to discuss. In response to these requests, we will collaborate closely with you to implement the appropriate adjustments.
 
Additionally, for a barrier-free and inclusive online experience, you can access u&u’s opportunities using accessibility software Recite Me at https://www.uandu.com/jobs.
 
Please submit your resume in Word format only.

